					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251586" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;" >Zyn</a></span> <span class="odate time_1421214907 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Jan 2015 05:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2206512">
									

<p>This thread is for helping people find pages that they remember reading, but don't remember by name.</p>
<p>Before you post here, ask yourself:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Have I used the search bar?</strong> The search bar is your friend, and is located to the top right of each site page. Try entering a few keywords in at a time, and browsing through the results.</li>
<li><strong>Have I checked the series lists?</strong> Sometimes you can find something by using a search function (Ctrl+F, Command+F, or the like) to go through the series lists (links on the left sidebar, under SCP Database). Try it a few times with keywords.</li>
<li><strong>Can I go to the chat for this?</strong> If you're looking for a quick answer, consider asking in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/chat-guide">IRC chatroom</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Things to keep in mind!</p>
<ul>
<li>This thread is for asking about <em>existing</em> pages. If you're asking &quot;has this been done before?&quot; because you want to write a new SCP, then make a thread in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-891087/help:general-advice">General Advice forum</a> to ask about basic ideas, or the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming forum</a> for more detailed, developed ideas.</li>
<li>Please be patient, and don't bump the thread. If you'd like to add anything to your posts, you can edit your comments using the &quot;edit&quot; function under the &quot;options&quot; tab to the lower right of every comment. That prevents spam buildup!</li>
<li>If you find that you're waiting far too long, PM a staff member, and we'll help you out.</li>
</ul>
<p>What additional information can I give that will help searchers? (None of these are required! Just suggestions, if you happen to remember these)</p>
<ul>
<li>If you're looking for an SCP, do you remember what numerical range it was in (e.g. series)? This can help narrow down searches if there are a few SCPs that are similar to what you're looking for.</li>
<li>Do you remember the author of the work, or if it was a rewrite or collaboration?</li>
<li>If you've already tried a few keyword searches, it's courteous to let readers/helpers know. A statement like &quot;I'm looking for [thing!] and I've tried the keywords [word!], [anotherword!] etc.&quot; will help the thread-goers help you!</li>
</ul>
<p>And of course, if you've got any questions, feel free to post in this thread and/or PM me (Zyn). Happy searching!</p>

