<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>From user TheBigDrCon4800:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>There is something on A thread about a SCP game on an island.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1008838/lost-connections#post-2128310">Link</a></p>
<p>From user jackuelar:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The scp I'm thinking of is a shard of a greek vase but i can't remember the effects of the scp.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Note: This one did get a response, but that response was very much not confident.<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1008838/lost-connections#post-2159304">Link</a></p>
<p>From user Kestin:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I remember reading what I think might have been a tale, but I'm not even sure if it was actually on the wiki, so I'll understand if it's not found. All I remember about it was that SCP-513 was involved, and 513-1 was more aggressive than in the article, and the Foundation thought that it was because the bell was more damaged (I think it was set in the future).</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1008838/lost-connections#post-2175865">Link</a></p>
<p>From user jackuelar:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Okay there are two articles that I cannot remember.</p>
<p>One is a DVD player that lets you control the whole film.</p>
<p>The other one is a bunch of dust mites that act like a sandstorm.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Note: someone responded with one of the inquiries, but couldn't find the other, and jackuelar did not confirm whether or not the linked answer was correct.<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1008838/lost-connections#post-2175907">Link</a></p>
<p>From user Americium241:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>What's that tale that has weird text alignment and is two narrators talking/arguing? I remember one part of it is like &quot;don't listen to them; you can tell by the alignment&quot; or something like that. I remember it's a little goofy, but I can't remember the Foundation-esque part of it. I can't remember enough keywords to find it with the search bar.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Notes: This did garner a response with multiple links, but Americium241 did not confirm or deny any of the links. Further, Americium241 has taken temporary leave of the wiki and likely isn't still searching.<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1008838/lost-connections#post-2180759">Link</a></p>
